stanford blsa conference progress and the legal profession stanford blsa conference progress and the legal profession the conference will exam the place of minorities in the legal profession specifically how much has changed and how much change is still needed this overarching question will be examined from the viewpoint of members of the judiciary and legal academia it will explore this theme through a variety of viewpoints such as the impact of positive or negative decisions on minority representation in these sectors the possible institutional structures or reforms in light of recent cases and the role of academia date and time saturday april 17 2010 11 00 am approximate duration of 7 hour s location faculty lounge stanford law school 559 nathan abbott way stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members category conferences symposia sponsor research institute of comparative studies in race and ethnicity contact 724 3468 cnqueen stanford edu admission free and open to the public registration is required http www stanford edu group blsa myform fb download add to personal calendar vcal record email event print use this permalink last modified april 13 2010
